            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="nar.03334.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
           
            <ab>Sept. 12, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>Alexander Johnston, Esq.</ab>
            <ab>Assistant Attorney Gen's office, Court of Claims</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>Will you report where upon the docket stands the case of Case and Van Wagenen, <hi rend="underline">vs.</hi> The United States&#8212;and what is the condition of preparation in that case?</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully, &amp;c</ab>
            <ab>A. T. Akerman, Attorney Gen'l.</ab>
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">Sup. Ct. Case</note>
            
           
            
        </body>
